# Planning and design docs

## Single source of truth

All architecture, phases, and implementation design live in committed repo files:

- **Center design:** [`docs/plan-workflow.md`](docs/plan-workflow.md) (target workflow by block; edit first for repo/block/CI changes)
- **Index:** [`docs/PLAN.md`](docs/PLAN.md) (shared replay foundation + links)
- **Mirror-merge:** [`docs/plan-sync-merge.md`](docs/plan-sync-merge.md) (`msys2-apiss` destination, Block 4 `yarn mirror-merge`)
- **Mirror-init:** [`docs/mirror-init.md`](docs/mirror-init.md) (Block 1: `yarn mirror-init`; [Tooling branch layout](docs/mirror-init.md#tooling-branch-layout))
- **Mirror-poll:** [`docs/mirror-poll.md`](docs/mirror-poll.md) (Block 2: `yarn mirror-poll`)

Edit the plan file that matches the area you are changing. Do not create other
parallel plan files unless the user explicitly asks.

## Do not use Cursor internal plans

Do **not** treat Cursor's internal plan feature as the project plan:

- No authoring or updating `~/.cursor/plans/*.plan.md` as the canonical design
- No copying plans to/from Cursor-only paths instead of the repo
- No "save to repo later" -- changes belong in `docs/PLAN.md` in the same turn

Internal plans are untracked, invisible in git, and easy to lose. They caused
confusion when they diverged from `docs/PLAN.md`.

## When design changes

1. Update [`docs/plan-workflow.md`](docs/plan-workflow.md) when blocks, repos, CI, or operator flows change
2. Update the area plan (`plan-sync-merge.md`, `mirror-init.md`) or [`PLAN.md`](docs/PLAN.md) when algorithm or module detail changes
2. Commit plan changes when the user asks (or as part of an agreed docs pass)
3. Reference these paths in code, rules, and PRs -- not Cursor plan URLs

## Agent behavior

- Read design from committed plan docs, not from conversation-only or Cursor-internal state
- Read block/repo/CI design from [`plan-workflow.md`](docs/plan-workflow.md) first
- Mirror-merge algorithm -> `plan-sync-merge.md` / `PLAN.md`; Block 1 detail -> `mirror-init.md`; Block 2 -> `mirror-poll.md`; Block 3 -> `plan-workflow.md`
- If committed plans and chat history disagree, the committed files win unless the user is actively revising them
